            "answer_text": "If two articles are sold at same price, one at a loss of R% and another at a profit of R%, there will always be a net loss of R^2/100. => Net loss = 20^2/100 = 4% Let SP of 1st article = 240 & SP of 2nd article = 240 CP of first article = 240/120 x 100 = 200 & CP of 2nd article = 240/80 x 100 = 300 Total Cost Price = 200 + 300 = 500 Total Selling Price = 240 + 240 = 480 Net Loss = 500 - 480 = 20 => 20/500 x 100 = 4% Note : Think a bit why I took Rs 240 as the common Selling Price :-) ",
